{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ensure fair grading for GCSE and A Level students in 2024 due to lost learning",
        "additional_details": "Students taking 2024 exams have experienced significant disruptions in their learning due to Covid lockdowns, self-isolation requirements, strikes, and school closures from RAAC and HACC concrete issues. These issues have had detrimental impacts on the amount of time students have been able to attend school for, which we believe has put them at a significant disadvantage to those who took exams pre-covid. High grade boundaries may disproportionately affect disadvantaged pupils.",
        "background": "We want the Government to work with Ofqual to ensure that students sitting exams in 2024 are given special consideration, such as additional marks or leniency with grade boundaries, to account for lost learning for this group.",
